HEADWORD: Snore
<hw>Snore</hw> <pr>(sn⟦omac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Snored</conjf> <pr>(sn⟦omac⟧rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Snoring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>snoren</ets>, AS. <ets>snora</ets> a snoring; akin to LG.
<ets>snoren</ets>, <ets>snorken</ets>, <ets>snurken</ets>, to snore, D.
<ets>snorken</ets>, G. <ets>schnarchen</ets> to snore,
<ets>schnarren</ets> to rattle, MHG. <ets>snarren</ets>, Sw.
<ets>snarka</ets> to snore, Icel. <ets>snarka</ets> to sputter, fizzle.
Cf. <er>Snarl</er> to growl, <er>Sneer</er>, <er>Snort</er>. See
<er>Snoring</er>.]</ety> <def>To breathe with a rough, hoarse, nasal
voice in sleep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snore</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Snore
<hw>Snore</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A harsh nasal noise made in
sleep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

